  "text": "u 12 corresponds to the prolonged part of the global solution u 1 to domain Ω 12 . As well, we introduce f g 12 = f g 2 , F g 12 = F g 2 and u g 12 = u g 2 the fictitious prolongation of f g 11 , F g 11 and u g 11 to Ω 12 , Γ F 12 and Γ u 12 , respectively. In this specific case of a void local model, we may take f g 12 = 0, F g 12 = 0 and u g 12 = 0. With these notations, we can reformulate problem [CITATION_1] over Ω 1 as follows:",
